AGI - The barometer of the Democratic Party, after weeks of storm, seems to finally turn to the serene. Effect of the eve of April 25 and the long bridge that gives the dems a climate from last day of school. But above all the fact that, archive lists and electoral logos, now in the PD they know that it is better to avoid polemics and woven quarrels to focus on the result of Europeans. In Transatlantic, the currents mix to wish "good April 25" and to make an appointment to resume the work. Under the apparent appeasement, however, the different souls of the Pd are filled with activity. The challenge of 9 June is those that can mark the future of a secretariat.
&nbsp;
The secretary refuses to fix asticelle, but in the Pd is indicated 20 percent as a minimum threshold > so as not to have to talk about defeat. However, in a few in the party they believe that Elly Schlein >rischi is stalled, even in the event of a negative result. Lack of alternatives, is explained. And then "no need," adds a dem source. The reasoning is that Schlein could remain in his place, perhaps "alonged" by a weight president who would subenter Stefano Bonaccini>, with the bags ready for Strasbourg. Of course, there is no reason to consider the European commitment as an essential element in the preservation of the office of President Pd by Bonaccini. However, for a current of thought present among the dems, the move of the president of Emilia-Romagna could provide the pretext to bring back to the field actively Paolo Gentiloni>.
&nbsp;
The Commissioner for Economic Affairs, in fact, ends his term in a year and a return to Rome would please many. Also for this reason, there are those who rob the hypothesis to a pious omen and those who read it under the lens of the movements between the currents. The idea of the name in the symbol, in fact, seems to have been born within the talks between Elly Schlein and Stefano Bonaccini. A solution with which the first intended to attract consensus even outside the perimeter of the party. The second was to secure the vote for the candidates of his area, otherwise at risk if the secretary had presented himself in all constituencies. A result that Bonaccini, among other things, obtained by guaranteeing strategic positions to its.&nbsp;
&nbsp;
Despite this, the President of the PD has been criticised for a part of the internal minority, which considers his opposition to the incisive secretariat. But it is above all the construction of the area and the work of rooting of People's Energy not to satisfy some prominent representatives of the minority. And the fact that it was precisely Bonaccini, as President Pd, to bring the proposal of the name in the direction did not contribute to shaping the souls. In fact: even very close to the president, like Stefano Lepri and Silvia Costa, intervened to stop the proposal immediately.
&nbsp;
If the minds are agitated in the minority, it is no better within the dem majority. The proposal on the electoral symbol >has provoked malumori also among members of the secretariat Pd like Peppe Provenzano and Marco Sarracino. But also Andrea Orlando crooked his nose with respect to the idea of entering the name of the secretary in the logo. And the former Labour Minister was the protagonist of a position that sounds a warning to Nazareno. Shortly before the vote in Brussels on the <a href="https://www.agi.it/estero/news/2024-04-23/new-patto-stabilita-ue-come-function-26142343/"> new Stability Pact</a>, Orlando had pointed out to journalists: "I hope that our group in Strasbourg will firmly reject the proposal for reform of the Stability Pact. A different vote would result in a negative judgement on the negotiating insipience of our government and on the betrayal that the EU Council has made with respect to the excellent Commission proposal, carried out thanks to the valuable work of Paolo Gentiloni". Words that are beaten with the line followed by the Pd delegation in Europe, <a href="https://www.agi.it/estero/news/2024-04-23/partiti-italiani-astenuti-patto-stabilita-ue-26144384/"> astenutasi dal ballo</a> per non 'rompere' con i resto del Pse, on one hand. And not to give the impression of wanting to defeat the work of Paolo Gentiloni, on the other.
&nbsp;
Done that yesterday, just a few hours from the vote, Orlando returns on the theme: "Gentiloni had made a proposal for reform of the Stability Pact which the EU Council amended and which initially reflected the spirit of the Next Generation and the challenges facing Europe," says Orlando. "A series of interventions from countries like France and Germany have reduced the instruments that Europe will have in the coming years." The result, for Orlando, is a "Stabilita Pact" that conflicts with a higher European ambition and with national interest, a quite paradoxical fact for a government that had to go to Europe to beat the fists on the table and ponder better conditions". A rejection for the government, then. And, of course, not a caress for the outgoing group in Brussels and for the secretary who blessed the path of abstention, after having harshly criticized the Covenant and the government for not having countered it sufficiently: "We will go against this compromise at the bottom," was in fact the line explicit by Schlein on March 5, a few hours from the free way of the European Council to the reform of the Covenant.

