The President of the Republic will then serve "the courage of incisive and courageous reforms > which are remitted to the next period after the European Parliament elections". "It will be the task of the European institutions and governments - the President has continued after the call to vote - to work to ensure that the Union is the protagonist in international life, bringing its contribution to you which is essentially the will of peace, collaboration and stability. We cannot remain in a condition in which Europe and all its member states as a result are in fact often spectators of what happens in the international community even in the face of events which sometimes suffer the consequences." &nbsp;

